lead_paragraph: Clutch putting and a final four-birdie flourish helped Jordan Spieth transform what might have been a 75 into a remarkable two-under-par 68 in Thursday's opening round of the WGC-Bridgestone Invitational in Ohio.

headline.print_headline: I Won the Battle in My Head Today, Says Grinding Spieth
